stories.title: A case of arrested development
stories.subTitle: Bangladesh v England, 3rd ODI, Dhaka
stories.summary: It wasn't quite a contest, and neither was it a write-off - but it was still a seven-wicket defeat, and for the third match running
stories.byline: The Wisden Verdict by Andrew Miller

stories.title: Meet the president
stories.subTitle: Bangladesh v England, 3rd ODI, Dhaka
stories.summary: As England's tour of Bangladesh came to a predictable close, the president and chief executive of ICC did an impromptu meet-and-greet session with the Dhaka crowd

stories.title: Collingwood and Flintoff lead England home
stories.subTitle: Bangladesh v England, 3rd ODI, Dhaka
stories.summary: England completed a 3-0 clean sweep against Bangladesh with another convincing win, by seven wickets, under the lights at Dhaka with Andrew Flintoff again voted Man of the Match
stories.byline: The Wisden Bulletin by Freddie Auld
